To: John C. Ratliff <br><br>
Thank you for the info. Do you know the name of a long Russian made snipers rifle used in Viet Nam? I have been looking for that information for awhile. <br>
During operation Foster Nov 1967 we were hit a number of times by a sniper using such a weapon. The sniper always got head shots and we lost several men to him. It wasn't until, long after the operation that we found out that it was a Russian using the sniper rifle who had an NVA liutenant assigned to him as a spotter. A high ranking defector who turned himself in confirmed this and the Russian or at least another Russian with a similiar accurate (long) rifle was later killled by a Marine sniper just north of DaNang sometimes later. That's all the information I have other then the sniper to have used that type of weapon would have had to have been in the Russain special forces and to have held the rank of major or above, 
